deck: A Canadian actor, well known for his roles in many television shows and movies.
description:
Comic Related Roles

Fillion is also known for his voice acting roles as Hal Jordan/Green Lantern in many DC animated films including:

Green Lantern: Emerald Knights (2011)

Justice League: Doom (2012)

Justice League: The Flashpoint Paradox (2013)

Justice League: Throne of Atlantis (2015)

He also voiced Steve Trevor in the Wonder Woman (2009) animated film.

Fillion also voiced the character Vigilante in the Justice League: Unlimited animated TV show
name: Nathan Fillion

description: What started out as a nice hobby quickly got out of hand. After some short stories in various Dutch anthologies, his first ongoing Dutch comic book series, Captain Roffa, was an instant success. Since then he has been breaking out of the borders of his beloved Holland with published work in several anthology comics in the States. When not drawing, Boykoesh likes to assault unsuspecting ducks and, like all Dutchmen, wear wooden clogs while picking tulips on his way to the windmill.
name: Boykoesh

description: Benjamin Bailey is a writer and storyteller with a passion for loud rock music, Ernest Hemingway, action movies, and Godzilla. He spent years living in van and playing rock n’ roll before finally settling down in the mountains with his beautiful wife and somewhat charming children. He firmly believes comic books can save the world.
name: Benjamin Bailey

deck:
Larry Lonsby Jr. is comic artist and creator of the well recieved "World of Tezlon" Originally published by Dark World Comics. A graduate of Saint Clair Community College Larry makes his home in Port Huron, MI.

Larry has released over 12 different Tezlon based books several with his recurring "Jaak Tate" scarecrow character. Set in a fantasy realm filled with elves and dwarves and cat people, Tezlon is born from larry's days as a role-playing enthusiast and based loosely on campaigns that he had done.
name: Larry Lonsby Jr.

description: Aaron Schoenke is an American film and television actor, screenwriter, film director, film editor, film producer, and cinematographer, best known for his Batman fan films.
name: Aaron Schoenke

deck: Editor and writer for Warren Publishing in the 1960s and 1970s.
description: Bill Parente was the editor and principal writer for Warren Publishing from July 1968 until mid-1970.
name: Bill Parente
